			<description><![CDATA[<p>Source4Style is seeking a seasoned internet marketing executive to be an integral part of the founding team as the company&rsquo;s first Chief Marketing Officer (CMO). The CMO will oversee all online and offline marketing operations - including but not limited to online advertising, search engine optimization, digital strategy, email marketing and offline promotional &amp; business development opportunities. The CMO will also be an integral part of the company&rsquo;s ongoing PR &amp; branding strategy.</p><p><strong>Experience</strong></p><p>Qualified candidates will have the following experience and skills:</p><ul><li>5-7 years of experience working specifically in online &amp; offline marketing;</li><li>Experience working in a fast-paced start-up;</li><li>Innovative, out-of-the-box creativity that fosters big ideas which can be executed on a comparatively small budget;</li><li>Analytical skills to review metrics on a daily basis and maximize online presence through Google, Google Adwords, Facebook, Twitter, Email marketing and other key channels;</li><li>Experience in the fashion &amp; technology space, with the know-how to build mutually-beneficial cross-promotional partnerships with other industry leaders;</li><li>Experience in project management of discrete technology buildouts with the purpose of increasing customers;</li><li>Editing and writing experience, and the ability to manage copywriters who deliver compelling copy;</li><li>Maintaining consistent, cutting edge and inspiring brand identity across all platforms - from daily emails to social media outreach; and</li><li>Basic, but not necessarily amazing, Photoshop, Illustrator and other Adobe software skills. And of course Excel, Powerpoint, Keynote.</li></ul><p><strong>Day-to-Day Responsibilities</strong><br />The CMO will work closely with the CEO, Director of Global Sourcing and Engineer. All of the day-to-day responsibilities should be directly tied to the overarching marketing goal - acquiring designer members from the 71 countries that Source4Style is already reaching. This will include everything from email marketing to online advertising to managing partnerships with other leading online fashion sites.</p><p><br />In addition to being a skilled multi-tasker, the ideal candidate will also have superb organizational &amp; project management skills.</p><p><strong>Company Culture</strong><br />Source4Style is a small team with a big vision - to create the first online tradeshow for global design inspiration. Our raison d&rsquo;etre is rooted in the social mission of expanding market access for SME suppliers around the world , connecting them to a rapidly-growing global community of fashion designers, interior designers and sourcing officials at major brands.</p><p>That said, our brand is sleek, fashion forward and constantly innovating to be a trusted &amp; curated source for global inspiration.</p><p>Qualified candidates will share in our mission and vision. They will be inspired by the chance to be an industry disrupter - making the world of fashion sourcing a bit flatter. And at the same time, they will also have a passion for and knowledge of the fashion &amp; design industry.</p><p>Members of the Source4Style team work hard, and they also work efficiently. We keep each other on track to focus on those activities that are directly related to our mission and month-by-month targets.</p><p>As a start-up, creativity, questioning, and proposed iterations to our strategy are not only encouraged, but required, from all team members.</p><p>Benefits include health insurance, professional development stipend, paid vacation and access to the employee stock option pool.</p>]]></description>
