			<description><![CDATA[<p>Source4Style is seeking a motivated and organized Community Manager to be an integral part of the company&rsquo;s growth across 71 countries. The Community Manager will oversee all aspects related to swatch and sample inventory and designer relations. S/he will also work closely with the CEO to implement key operational processes including accounting, packaging, inventory management and management of the company&rsquo;s CRM software.</p><p><strong>Experience</strong></p><p>Qualified candidates will have the following experience and skills:</p><ul><li>2-3 years administrative experience;</li><li>Experience working in a fast-paced company with a small team;</li><li>Knowledge of Excel, Salesforce &amp; basic inventory management;</li><li>Basic knowledge of textiles and materials sourcing;</li><li>Experience working directly with customers - on the phone, in-person and over email;</li><li>Maintaining a consistent, clear and friendly brand voice through all customer and designer relations;</li><li>Experience working across cultures and countries;</li><li>Good and concise writing skills with a keen attention to detail</li></ul><p><strong>Day-to-Day Responsibilities</strong></p><p>The Community Manager will work closely with the CEO and Director of Global Sourcing. Day-to-day responsibilities include fulfillment of swatch and sample orders, management of swatch inventory, preparing POs for Source4Style suppliers, assisting designers as they source on Source4Style.com, communicating technical glitches to the company&rsquo;s Engineer and maintaining clean organizational processes.</p><p>In addition to being a skilled multi-tasker, the ideal candidate will also have superb organizational &amp; project management skills.</p><p><strong>Company Culture</strong></p><p>Source4Style is a small team with a big vision - to create the first online tradeshow for global design inspiration. Our raison d&rsquo;etre is rooted in the social mission of expanding market access for SME suppliers around the world, connecting them to a rapidly-growing global community of fashion designers, interior designers and sourcing officials at major brands.</p><p>That said, our brand is fashion forward, inspirational and constantly innovating to be a trusted &amp; curated source for global inspiration.</p><p>Qualified candidates will share in our mission and vision. They will be inspired by the chance to be an industry disrupter - making the world of fashion sourcing a bit flatter. And at the same time, they will also have a passion for and knowledge of the fashion &amp; design industry.</p><p>Members of the Source4Style team work hard, and they also work efficiently. We keep each other on track to focus on those activities that are directly related to our mission and month-by-month targets.</p><p>As a start-up, creativity, questioning, and proposed iterations to our strategy are not only encouraged, but required, from all team members.</p><p>This will start as a part-time position, with the potential to develop quickly into a full-time position within 2-3 months.</p><p>Start-up salary will be both competitive and commensurate with experience.</p>]]></description>
