			<description><![CDATA[<p>Source4Style is seeking an engineer to be an integral part of the company&rsquo;s rapid growth. The Engineer will work closely with the CEO &amp; Lead Developer to maintain the company&rsquo;s custom wholesale ordering technology, continuously innovate and iterate to make Source4Style.com the most user-friendly sourcing site on the web, and manage the technological buildout of a platform facilitating transactions between suppliers in 24 countries and designers in 71 countries.</p><p>The Engineer will work out of Source4Style&rsquo;s office in midtown Manhattan.</p><p><strong>Experience</strong><br />Qualified candidates will have the following experience and skills:</p><ul><li>Development of customer-facing features - building seamless user experience and elegant back-end code;</li><li>UI design that enhances usability and facilitates the maximum number of transactions;</li><li>Experience working on the Magento eCommerce Platform and Wordpress;</li><li>Proficiency in PHP development;</li><li>Data analytics - building the information structure to effectively capture key points of data from customers and use that data to personalize the Source4Style experience;</li><li>Experience working in a fast-paced start-up with a small team;</li><li>Experience managing off-shore developers;</li><li>Acquiring feedback from customers through surveys and regular review of analytics;</li><li>Quickly iterating based on customer feedback and analytics</li></ul><p><strong>Day-to-Day Responsibilities</strong><br />The Engineer will work directly with the CEO, CMO &amp; Lead Developer. On a daily basis, the Engineer will be reviewing customer analytics, enhancing the UI and userflow, managing the buildout of new features (i.e. product reviews, launch of new materials categories, integration of live chat), and working with the CEO to implement key features related to the compliance of a global ecommerce platform.</p><p>In addition to being a skilled multi-tasker, the ideal candidate will also have superb organizational &amp; project management skills.</p><p><strong>Company Culture</strong><br />Source4Style is a small team with a big vision - to create the first online tradeshow for global design inspiration. Our raison d&rsquo;etre is rooted in the social mission of expanding market access for SME suppliers around the world, connecting them to a rapidly-growing global community of fashion designers, interior designers and sourcing officials at major brands.</p><p>Qualified candidates will share in our mission and vision. They will be inspired by the chance to be an industry disrupter - making the world of fashion sourcing a bit flatter. They will see the potential to use the latest technologies to disrupt a market dominated by offline tradeshows.</p><p>Members of the Source4Style team work hard, and they also work efficiently. We keep each other on track to focus on those activities that are directly related to our mission and month-by-month targets.</p><p>As a start-up, creativity, questioning, and proposed iterations to our strategy are not only encouraged, but required, from all team members.</p><p>This will start as a part-time position, with the potential to develop quickly into a full-time position within 2-3 months.<br />Benefits include health insurance, professional development stipend, paid vacation and access to the employee stock pool.</p>]]></description>
